In a proclamation issued on May 31, 2018, President Donald Trump declared June 2018 as National Ocean Month in the United States. The proclamation highlights the importance of the ocean and coastal waters to the nation's identity, wealth, and security. It emphasizes the economic benefits and job opportunities provided by the ocean industries and calls for the responsible and effective utilization of the United States Exclusive Economic Zone (EEZ), which is currently underutilized. The proclamation also emphasizes the need to explore, map, and inventory the nation's waters, as well as develop advanced observational technologies and forecasting capabilities. Overall, the proclamation aims to promote economic competitiveness, enhance national security, and ensure American prosperity through the sustainable use of ocean resources.